README FILE
Week 6 Consolidation Task: Python Task Manager 

Add task function: 
The user must enter something in the box to proceed.
The function will return to the main menu if the input text is empty or only a blank space is entered.

List Task  function:
This lists all tasks with their completion status indication, task id number, and task description, then displays the main menu
If there are no tasks, an error message is displayed, and the user returns to the main menu.

Mark Complete function:
This lists existing tasks, and the user can mark one complete. The programme then returns to the main menu.

Main menu:
This lists the above functionalities, assigning a value to each. The user enters their choice as a number (as a string)
The function is recursive, and calls itself if an invalid choice is entered.

